article.headline: S. Illinois 73, Illinois St. 62
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) -- Jamaal Tatum scored 22 points Saturday to lead Southern Illinois to a 73-72 comeback win over Illinois State. The Salukis (17-5, 8-3 Missouri Valley), trailed 31-25 at halftime, after the Redbirds held them to a 37.5 field goal percentage while Illinois State shot over 50 percent from the field. Southern Illinois' offense broke through in the second half, shooting 64 percent from field, while hitting six of their 10 three-point attempts. Illinois State (11-11, 3-8) couldn't keep up, despite improving their field goal percentage in the second half to 55 percent, and hitting 6-of-8 three-pointers. Randal Falker scored 19 points and blocked five shots for the Salukis, and Tony Young added 16. Levi Dyer led the Redbirds with 18 points, with Osiris Eldridge adding 17 points and grabbing eight rebounds.
